THIS MODIFICATION IS TO DEOBLIGATE EXCESS FUNDS OFF DO 0051 DUE TO REDUCED UNIT PRICES AS A RESULT OF INCORPORATION OF SNE-U ECP VIA MODIFICATION P00102.

ASTRONAUTS LOSE CONSIDERABLE BONE MASS DURING LONG DURATION SPACEFLIGHT. THESE LOSSES ARE ONE OF THE MAJOR CONCERNS FOR PROPOSEDEXPLORATION CLASS MISSIONS TO THE MOON, MARS, AND NEAR EARTH OBJECTS DUE TO THE INCREASE IN FRACTURE RISK ASSOCIATED WITH REDUCED BONE STRENGTH. THESE LOSSES ARE SEEN EVEN WITH THE INTERVENTION OF CURRENT EXERCISE COUNTERMEASURES. ALTHOUGH IT IS POSSIBLE THAT THE NEWEST EXERCISE MACHINE, THE ADVANCED RESISTIVE EXERCISE DEVICE (ARED), WILL BE MORE EFFECTIVE IN PREVENTING BONE AND MUSCLE LOSSES, ITS SIZE MAY BE PROHIBITIVE IN BRINGING IT ON INTERPLANETARY MISSIONS. IN ORDER FOR ASTRONAUTS TO BE ABLE TO PERFORM SUCCESSFUL EXPLORATION TASKS, THEY NEED TO ARRIVE AT THEIR DESTINATIONS HEALTHY AND CAPABLE OF DOING WORK. BECAUSE OF THIS, NEW COUNTERMEASURES WILL NEED TO BE DEVELOPED TO PREVENT MUSCULOSKELETAL DECONDITIONING. THE GOAL OF THIS PROPOSAL IS TO MEET THIS NEED BY PRODUCING A WEARABLE COUNTERMEASURE SUIT. THE SUITS PRIMARY GOAL WILL BE TO IMPOSE STATIC LOADING, SIMILAR TO THAT PRODUCED BY GRAVITY, ON THE USER. IN ADDITION, INCORPORATING A DYNAMIC LOADING COMPONENT, SUCH AS A FORM OF VIBRATION, MAY ENHANCE THE EFFECTIVENESS OF THE SUIT. FINALLY, INTEGRATING THE SUIT WITH EXISTING COUNTERMEASURES COULD SERVE TO IMPROVE THE OVERALL EFFICACY OF THE ENTIRE COUNTERMEASURE PROGRAM. WHILE ASTRONAUTS CURRENTLY EXERCISE FOR AROUND 2 HOURS, THIS SUIT COULD BE WORN FOR A LONGER PERIOD OF TIME, INCLUDING WHILE THE ASTRONAUTS ARE PERFORMING OTHER TASKS. THE SUITS WILL ALSO BE LIGHTWEIGHT AND EASILY PACKABLE, WHICH IS A MAJOR CONSIDERATION FOR SPACE EXPLORATION MISSIONS. THE RESEARCH OBJECTIVES OF THIS PROPOSAL ARE AS FOLLOWS: 1. TO PRODUCE A COMPREHENSIVE MODEL OF SUIT-BODY INTERACTIONS TO AID IN SUIT DESIGN 2. TO INVESTIGATE THE INTEGRATION OF THE SUIT WITH EXISTING COUNTERMEASURES 3. TO INVESTIGATE FORMS OF DYNAMIC LOADING, AND THEIR EFFECTS ON SUBJECT COMFORT AND PERFORMANCE 4. TO BUILD AND CHARACTERIZE PROTOTYPE COUNTERMEASURE SUITS THE MODEL FROM AIM 1 WILL BE CREATED USING MATLAB AND BODY MODELING SOFTWARE, AND WILL BE USED TO INFORM SUIT DESIGN. IT WILL BE USED TO COMPUTE THE EFFECTS OF INTEGRATING THE SUIT WITH EXISTING COUNTERMEASURES ON OVERALL SUIT CHARACTERISTICS. DYNAMIC LOADING MECHANISMS WILL BE EVALUATED ON THEIR LOADING QUALITIES AND INFLUENCE ON SUBJECT COMFORT AND PERFORMANCE. AFTER THE SUITS ARE CONSTRUCTED, THEIR LOADING AND COMFORT TRAITS WILL BE CHARACTERIZED. THE GRAVITY LOADING COUNTERMEASURE SKINSUIT WILL REDUCE THE MUSCULOSKELETAL DECONDITIONING SEEN DURING LONG DURATION SPACEFLIGHT, ALLOWING FOR A MORE ROBUST AND EFFECTIVE EXPLORATION PROGRAM. THE TECHNOLOGIES DEVELOPED IN THIS PROPOSAL WILL ALSO HAVE APPLICATIONS IN THE MEDICAL FIELD, FOR TREATING BED REST PATIENTS AND IN HEALING MUSCULOSKELETAL INJURIES.

doc.ContractDescription: KEYWORDS: NITROGEN-VACANCY DEFECT, MAGNETOMETRY, QUANTUM INFORMATION, QUANTUM MEMORY, DLCZ SCHEME, BIOCHEMICAL SENSING, NANOPHOTONICS, FLUORESCENCE SPECTROSCOPY, FRET WITH RECENT TALKS OF THE CONSTELLATION PROGRAM EMBARKING ON PLANETARY EXPLORATION, THE NEED FOR COMPACT, HIGHLY-INTEGRATED COMMUNICATION AND REMOTE SENSING HARDWARE TOOLS GROWS MORE AND MORE PRESSING. MY RESEARCH INTO THE APPLICATIONS OF ENGINEERED, SINGLE-CRYSTAL DIAMOND ADDRESSES THIS STRONG NEED FOR AN ON-CHIP QUANTUM NETWORK AND SENSING ELECTRIC AND MAGNETIC FIELDS AT NANOMETER DISTANCES. DIAMOND IS A PROMISING CANDIDATE FOR THESE APPLICATIONS BECAUSE IT HAS ALREADY BEEN DEMONSTRATED TO BE WORK IN A RANGE OF APPLICATIONS SUCH AS RADIATION HARD ELECTRONICS [1-3], ELECTRIC FIELD EMITTERS [2-3], DIAMOND MICRO-MECHANICAL DEVICES [4-5], HIGHTEMPERATURE, HIGH-VOLTAGE, AND HIGH-FREQUENCY OPTOELECTRONICS [1,6-7], MAGNETIC [4] AND ELECTRIC FIELD SENSORS [5], SPIN-BASED SOLID-STATE CLOCKS AND FREQUENCY STANDARDS [8], AND QUANTUM INFORMATION PROCESSING (QIP) DEVICES [9, I OJ. I AIM TO FIRST UNDERSTAND AND DEVELOP SOLID STATE SENSORS THAT CAN ALSO OPERATE AT OR BEYOND THE STANDARD QUANTUM LIMIT (SQL) [14]. SUCH SENSORS WOULD HAVE SENSITIVITIES LIMITED ONLY BY THE HEISENBERG UNCERTAINTY PRINCIPLE AND COULD ENABLE NEW APPLICATIONS OF ENTANGLEMENT; FOR INSTANCE, THROUGH THE DEVELOPMENT OF LONG-DISTANCE QUANTUM COMMUNICATION BETWEEN ENTANGLED SPINS NETWORKS. IN THE PROCESS OF DEVELOPING SUCH SYSTEMS, I WILL EMPLOY ELECTRON SPINS IN DIAMOND AS A PRACTICAL MAGNETOMETER THAT SURPASSES THE CURRENT SENSITIV ITY BARRIER AT ROOM TEMPERATURES. THE NEGATIVELY-CHARGED NITROGEN-VACANCY DEFECT (NY) IN SINGLE CRYSTAL DIAMONDS IS CURRENTLY THE TOP CANDIDATE FOR MEASURING MAGNETIC FIELDS AT THE SQL WHILE ALSO OPERATING AT ROOM TEMPERATURE [ 15]. THE NV- HAS A SPIN COHERENCE TIME (~ I MS) THAT EXCEEDS THAT OF ANY OTHER SOLID STATE SYSTEM [E.G. QUANTUM DOTS (QD)] AND IS RIVALED ONLY BY TRAPPED IONS. I BELIEVE IN THE VISION OF OUR LAB TO ENGINEER CHIP-INTEGRATED SOLUTIONS FOR TRANSPORTATION (VIA PHOTONS), STORAGE (VIA NUCLEAR SPINS), AND PROCESSING (VIA MICROWAVES) OF INFORMATION. THOUGH MANY OF THE MAJOR PROCESSES FOR THIS VISION HAVE BEEN EXPERIMENTALLY REALIZED IN THE LAST TWO DECADES ON INDIVIDUAL ATOMS, MUCH MORE WORK REMAINS TO BE DONE TO CULMINATE IN A MULTIFUNCTIONAL LIGHT-MATTER INTERFACE BASED ENTIRELY IN A SO LID STATE SYSTEM.
